A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating and commending Nellie Klodner; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Nellie Klodner received the 2024 Inclusion Award from Georgia Tech's K-12
3 InVenture Prize State Finals at the Raytheon Technologies Invention Convention United
4 States Nationals; and
5 WHEREAS, Ms. Klodner is a diligent, hard-working student from Panter Elementary
6 School; and
7 WHEREAS, with the help of Anna Borsh, Ms. Klodner created the app "Grocery Eyes,"
8 which helps visually impaired people navigate through the grocery store more easily; and
9 WHEREAS, both Ms. Klodner and Ms. Borsh created the app in the hope that visually
10 impaired people can gain more independence through using the app's navigation,
11 microphone, and camera features to help locate items; and
12 WHEREAS, prior to winning the 2024 Inclusion Award at the United States Nationals,
13 "Grocery Eyes" won the same title from the state level competition where each student won
14 an Amazon tablet; and
